A 27-year-old man died Sunday after a steel rod hit him at a construction site in Tassia, Nairobi. Allan Munyao died on the spot after the rod fell and hit him on the head. Police say they are investigating the incident. The body was moved to the mortuary. Such accidents are common at construction sites due to negligence and lack of protection. Officials from National Construction Authority were set to visit the site as part of the probe into the accident. Nairobi acting police boss James Mugera said experts are investigating the incident. “We want to know what and how it happened,” he said. Meanwhile, police are investigating an incident in which a Chinese national claims she lost her Sh3 million and jewelry from her house in Kileleshwa, Nairobi. The woman identified as Lim Mei, a supplier of merchant goods, told police she left for dinner on Saturday, but when she came back, she found the money missing. The said thieves used a spare key to open the door to her bedroom and safe to access the cash and valuables. She told police she also lost a metallic panty to the thieves. Police suspect inside job over the incident. Investigations into the incident are ongoing.